Jakadan Amurka ya zargi kasar Sin da cin zarafin "tallace-tallace"
Wata mako bayan wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wata sanarwa mai shafuka hudu a wata jaridar Amurka da ke shelar amfanin cinikin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka wajen yada labaran.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi magana game da karin kudin biyan kudi na China Daily a cikin Des Moines Register, jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a jihar Iowa, bayan ya zargi kasar Sin da tsoma baki a zaben majalisar dokokin Amurka da za a yi a ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, abin da kasar Sin ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna abin da jami'an kasar suka bayyana a Reuters a matsayin wani sabon mataki na yakin neman zabe na Washington na matsa lamba ga kasar Sin.
Duk da yake yana da kyau gwamnatocin ƙasashen waje su ba da tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna cikin faɗaɗa yaƙin kasuwanci wanda ke nuna matakin haraji a kan shigo da su.
Masana a kasar Sin da Amurka sun ce an tsara harajin da kasar Sin ta yi a farkon yakin kasuwanci don cutar da masu fitar da kaya daga jihohi kamar Iowa, wanda ke goyon bayan Jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, daya daga cikin manyan masu fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kuma 'yan kasuwa lahani.
Wani labarin da Branstad ya wallafa a jaridar Moines Register a ranar Lahadi ya nuna cewa kasar Sin "ta kara da wannan harin ta hanyar yada tallan talla a cikin jaridar Amurka kyauta".
"A cikin yada labaransa, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi amfani da al'adar Amirka ta 'yancin yin magana da kuma yada labarai ta hanyar wallafa wani sanarwa mai biyan kuɗi a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A akasin haka, a gidan jaridu da ke kusa da wannan titi a Beijing, akwai muryoyin rashin amincewa da shi kuma babu wani ainihin tunani game da ra'ayoyin da ke tsakanin 'yan kasar Sin game da tattalin arzikin kasar Sin, tun da kafofin watsa labarai suna ƙarƙashin ikon jam'iyyar kwaminisancin kasar Sin", in ji shi.
Hakazalika, ya ce "daya daga cikin manyan jaridu a kasar Sin ya ƙi yin tayin" ya buga labarinsa, ko da yake bai tabbatar da cewa jaridar ce ba.
